<div class="comment-wrapper"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8aa3a9da9a32d3e98805b4a5409e4cee?s=50"></div><header><strong>Remove Failable Initializers</strong> from <string>Anton Zhilin</string> &lt;antonyzhilin at gmail.com&gt;<p>March  6, 2016 at 12:00:00pm</p></header><div class="content"><p>Without adding more arguments, I agree with what has been said before me.<br>Failable initializers replace factory methods in other languages, fitting<br>into Swift error model.<br>Basically, init() behaves as  `(Args)-&gt;Self`  function, and should be able<br>to express errors as other functions: `(Args)-&gt;Self?`, `(Args)<br>throws-&gt;Self`.<br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-evolution/attachments/20160306/930d5ac7/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></div>    </main>
